      <h1 class='title'>AMENDMENTS OF THE FAMILY HOMES AND DOMESTIC VIOLENCE (NORTHERN IRELAND) ORDER (S.I. 1998/1071 (N.I. 6)</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='grand-committee-report-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HL Deb 17 May 2004 vol 661 cc323-9GC</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_323gc' title='Col. 323GC &mdash; HL Deb 17 May 2004 vol 661 c323GC' name='column_323gc' href='#column_323gc' rel='bookmark'>323GC</a>
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04103'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_714' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        1 (1) Amend Article 2 (interpretation) as follows.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04104'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_715' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (2) In paragraph (2), after the definition of "health" insert&#x2014;
        <q>"home rights" has the meaning given by Article 4;".</q>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04105'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_716' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (3) In the definition of "matrimonial charge" in that paragraph, after "matrimonial" insert "or civil partnership".
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04106'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_717' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (4) Omit the definition of "matrimonial home rights" in that paragraph.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04107'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_718' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (5) In the definition of "relative" in that paragraph&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) in paragraphs (a) and (b) for "spouse or former spouse" substitute "spouse, former spouse, civil partner or former civil partner", and</li>
        <li>(b) after "were married to each other" inset "or were civil partners of each other".</li></ol>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04108'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_719' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (6) After paragraph (2)(g) insert&#x2014;
        <q>(h) the <a href="/acts/civil-partnership-act-2004">Civil Partnership Act 2004</a>.</q>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04109'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_720' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (7) In paragraph (7), after "matrimonial" insert "or civil partnership".
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04110'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_721' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        2 (1) Amend Article 3 (meaning of "cohabitees", "relevant child" and "associated persons") as follows.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04111'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_722' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (2) For paragraph (1)(a) substitute&#x2014;
        <q>(a) ""cohabitees" are two persons who are neither married to each other nor civil partners of each other but are living together as husband and wife or as if they were civil partners;".</q>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04112'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_723' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (3) In paragraph (1)(b), after "have subsequently married each other" insert "or become civil partners of each other".
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04113'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_724' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (4) After paragraph (3)(a) insert&#x2014;
        <q>(aa) they are or have been civil partners of each other;".</q>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04114'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_725' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (5) After paragraph (3)(e) insert&#x2014;
        <q>(eza) they have entered into a civil partnership agreement (as defined by section (<span class="italic">Civil partnership agreements unenforceable</span>) of the <a href="/acts/civil-partnership-act-2004">Civil Partnership Act 2004</a>) (whether or not that agreement has been terminated);".</q>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04115'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_726' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        3 (1) Amend Article 4 (rights concerning matrimonial home where one spouse has no estate, etc.) as follows.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04116'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_727' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (2) In paragraph (1)&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) in sub-paragraph (a)&#x2014;</li>
        <ol>
        <li>(i) after "one spouse" insert "or civil partner ("A")", and</li>
        <li>(ii) for "that spouse" substitute "A",</li></ol>
        <li>(b) in sub-paragraph (b), after "other spouse" insert "or civil partner ("B")".</li></ol>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04117'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_728' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (3) In paragraph (2)&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) for "the spouse not so entitled" substitute "B",</li>
        <li>(b) for "("matrimonial home rights")" substitute "("home rights")", and</li>
        <col>GC 324</col>
        <li>(c) in sub-paragraph (a), for "the other spouse" substitute "A".</li></ol>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04118'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_729' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (4) In paragraph (3)&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) for "a spouse" and for "that spouse" substitute "B", and</li>
        <li>(b) for "the other spouse" (in both places) substitute "A".</li></ol>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04119'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_730' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (5) In paragraph (4)&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) for "A spouse's" substitute "B's",</li>
        <li>(b) in sub-paragraph (a), for "by the other spouse as the other spouse's" substitute "by A as A's", and</li>
        <li>(c) in sub-paragraph (b)&#x2014;</li>
        <ol>
        <li>(i) for "the spouse occupies the dwelling-house as that spouse's" substitute "B occupies the dwelling-house as B's", and</li>
        <li>(ii) for "by the other spouse as the other spouse's" substitute "by A as A's".</li></ol></ol>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04120'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_731' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (6) In paragraph (5)&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) for "a spouse ("the first spouse")" substitute "B", and</li>
        <li>(b) in sub-paragraph (b), for "the other spouse ("the second spouse")" substitute "A",</li>
        <li>(c) for "the second spouse" (in both places) substitute "A", and</li>
        <li>(d) for "the first spouse" substitute "B".</li></ol>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04121'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_732' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (7) In paragraph (6)&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) for "a spouse" substitute "B", and</li>
        <li>(b) for "the other spouse" (in both places) substitute "A".</li></ol>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04122'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_733' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (8) In paragraph (7), for the words from first "which" to the end substitute "which&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) in the case of spouses, has at no time been, and was at no time intended by them to be, a matrimonial home of theirs; and</li>
        <li>(b) in the case of civil partners, has at no time been, and was at no time intended by them to be, a civil partnership home of theirs."</li></ol>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04123'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_734' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (9) In paragraph (8)&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) for "A spouse's matrimonial home rights" substitute "B's home rights",</li>
        <li>(b) in sub-paragraph (a), after "marriage" insert "or civil partnership", and</li>
        <li>(c) in sub-paragraph (b), for "the other spouse" substitute "A".</li></ol>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04124'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_735' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (10) In paragraph (9)&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) for "a spouse" substitute "a person",</li>
        <li>(b) for "matrimonial home rights" substitute "home rights", and</li>
        <li>(c) after "spouses" insert "or civil partners".</li></ol>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04125'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_736' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (11) In the heading to Article 4, for "matrimonial home where one spouse" substitute "home where one spouse or civil partner" and, in the preceding cross-heading, after "matrimonial" insert "or civil partnership".
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04126'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_737' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        4 (1) Amend Article 5 (effect of matrimonial home rights as charge on dwelling-house) as follows.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04127'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_738' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (2) In paragraph (1), for "marriage, one spouse" substitute "marriage or civil partnership, A".
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04128'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_739' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (3) In paragraph (2), for "The other spouse's matrimonial home rights" substitute "B's home rights".
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04129'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_740' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (4) In paragraph (3)&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) in sub-paragraph (a), for "the spouse so entitled" substitute "A", and</li>
        <li>(b) in sub-paragraph (b), after "marriage" insert 'or of the formation of the civil partnership".</li></ol>
      </p>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_325gc' title='Col. 325GC &mdash; HL Deb 17 May 2004 vol 661 c325GC' name='column_325gc' href='#column_325gc' rel='bookmark'>325GC</a>
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04130'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_741' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (5) In paragraph (4)&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) for "a spouse's matrimonial home rights" substitute "B's home rights",</li>
        <li>(b) for "the other spouse" substitute "A", and</li>
        <li>(c) for "either of the spouses" substitute "A or B".</li></ol>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04131'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_742' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (6) In paragraph (5), for "the other spouse" substitute "A".
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04132'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_743' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (7) In paragraph (6), for "the spouses" substitute "A and B".
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04133'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_744' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (8) In paragraph (7)&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) for "a spouse's matrimonial home rights" substitute "B's home rights",</li>
        <li>(b) in sub-paragraph (a), for "the other spouse" substitute "A", and</li>
        <li>(c) in sub-paragraph (b), after "marriage" insert "or civil partnership".</li></ol>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04134'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_745' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (9) In paragraph (8)&#x2014;
        <ol>
        <li>(a) in sub-paragraph (a), for "a spouse's matrimonial home rights" substitute "B's home rights", and</li>
        <li>(b) for "the other spouse" (in both places) substitute "A".</li></ol>
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04135'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_746' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (10) In the heading to Article 5, for "matrimonial home rights" substitute "home rights".
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04136'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_747' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        5 (1) Amend Article 6 (registration, etc. of matrimonial charge) as follows.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04137'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_748' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (2) In paragraphs (1), (3), (4), (5) and (6), after "matrimonial" insert "or civil partnership".
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04138'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_749' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (3) In the heading to Article 6, after "matrimonial" insert "or civil partnership".
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04139'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_750' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        6 (1) Amend Article 7 (restriction on registration where spouse entitled to more than one matrimonial charge) as follows.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04140'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_751' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (2) In paragraphs (1), (2) and (3), after "spouse" (in each place) insert "or civil partner".
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04141'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_752' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (3) In paragraphs (1), (2), (3) and (4), after "matrimonial" (in each place) insert "or civil partnership".
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04142'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_753' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (4) In paragraph (3), for "matrimonial home rights" substitute "home rights".
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04143'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_754' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (5) In the heading to Article 7, after "matrimonial" insert "or civil partnership".
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04144'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_755' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        7 (1) Amend Article 8 (cancellation of registration of matrimonial charge before completion of disposal of dwelling-house) as follows.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04145'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_756' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (2) In paragraphs (1) and (2), after "matrimonial" insert "or civil partnership".
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04146'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_757' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (3) In the heading to Article 8, after "matrimonial" insert "or civil partnership".
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04147'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_758' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        8 (1) Amend Article 9 (cancellation of registration after termination of marriage, etc.) as follows.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04148'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_759' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (2) In paragraph (1), for "matrimonial charge" substitute "matrimonial or civil partnership charge".
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04149'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_760' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (3) In paragraphs (1)(a), (2)(a) and (b) and (3), after "spouse" insert "or civil partner".
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04150'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_761' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (4) In paragraphs (1)(b), (2)(a) and (4), after "marriage" (in each place) insert "or civil partnership".
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04151'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_762' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (5) In paragraphs (1)(c), (2), (3) and (4), after "matrimonial" (in each place) insert "or civil partnership".
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04152'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_763' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (6) In paragraph (1)(c), for "spouse's matrimonial home rights" substitute "spouse's or civil partner's home rights".
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04153'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_764' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (7) In the heading to Article 9, after "marriage" insert "or civil partnership".
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04154'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_765' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        9 (1) Amend Article 10 (release of matrimonial home rights and postponement of priority of matrimonial charge) as follows.
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04155'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_766' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        (2) In paragraph (1), for "spouse entitled to matrimonial home rights" substitute "spouse or civil partner entitled to home rights".
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0661P0-04156'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0661P0_20040517_GCR_767' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
